  "local_port": 54156,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the top 10 inspirational movies of the 21st century?",
  "response": "Here is a list of 10 highly inspirational movies from the 21st century, based on their impact, popularity, and critical acclaim:\n\n1. **\"The Pursuit of Happyness\" (2006)**\n   - **Director:** Gabriele Muccino\n   - **Synopsis:** Based on a true story, this film follows Chris Gardner, a struggling salesman who becomes homeless with his young son but never gives up on his dream of a better life.\n\n2. **\"The Shawshank Redemption\" (1994)**\n   - **Director:** Frank Darabont\n   - **Synopsis:** Although released in the late 20th century, its inspirational message and themes continue to resonate strongly into the 21st century. It tells the story of a young man wrongfully convicted of murder and his enduring friendship with a fellow inmate.\n\n3. **\"The Blind Side\" (2009)**\n   - **Director:** John Lee Hancock\n   - **Synopsis:** This film is based on the true story of Michael Oher, a homeless and traumatized boy who becomes an All-American football player with the help of a caring woman and her family.\n\n4. **\"Slumdog Millionaire\" (2008)**\n   - **Director:** Danny Boyle\n   - **Synopsis:** An inspiring tale of a young man from the slums of Mumbai who becomes a contestant on the Indian version of \"Who Wants to Be a Millionaire?\" and how his life experiences lead him to the answers.\n\n5. **\"A Beautiful Mind\" (2001)**\n   - **Director:** Ron Howard\n   - **Synopsis:** Based on the life of John Nash, a mathematician who struggles with schizophrenia but goes on to win a Nobel Prize, this film showcases the triumph of the human spirit.\n\n6. **\"Freedom Writers\" (2007)**\n   - **Director:** Richard LaGravenese\n   - **Synopsis:** Inspired by a true story, this movie follows a teacher who inspires her at-risk students to overcome their troubled lives and academic challenges through writing.\n\n7. **\"The King's Speech\" (2010)**\n   - **Director:** Tom Hooper\n   - **Synopsis:** This film tells the story of King George VI, who struggles with a stammer and overcomes it with the help of an unorthodox speech therapist, just in time to lead his country through World War II.\n\n8. **\"Invictus\" (2009)**\n   - **Director:** Clint Eastwood\n   - **Synopsis:** Focused on Nelson Mandela's efforts to unite South Africa through the 1995 Rugby World Cup, this film highlights themes of leadership and reconciliation.\n\n9. **\"Cinderella Man\" (2005)**\n   - **Director:** Ron Howard\n   - **Synopsis:** Based on the true story of James J. Braddock, a boxer who makes a comeback during the Great Depression to become a symbol of hope for many.\n\n10. **\"Soul Surfer\" (2011)**\n    - **Director:** Sean McNamara\n    - **Synopsis:** This film is based on the true story of Bethany Hamilton, a young surfer who loses her arm in a shark attack but returns to professional surfing, inspiring many with her courage and determination.\n\nThese movies span a range of genres and themes but are united by their inspirational narratives and messages of hope, resilience, and triumph over adversity.",
